because they will buy our stock, so we can always pay back our debts=E2=80=
=9D might be more or less true even though it doesn=E2=80=99t make much sen=
se.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The next step is to separate this theor=
y entirely from cash flows, companies, etc. Just like: =E2=80=9CWe have iss=
ued shares of nothing, and as long as people continue to buy those shares o=
f nothing at some positive price, our debt will always be money-good.=E2=80=
=9D=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The way an algorithmic stablecoin=
 works is that somebody creates two cryptocurrency=C2=A0tokens, let=E2=80=
=99s call them Dollarcoin and Sharecoin. And they write a white paper that =
says =E2=80=9CDollarcoins=C2=A0will always be worth $1, and if they are eve=
